cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language generation and explicitly models syntactic information. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for generating sentences using a VAE. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves generating natural language using a machine learning model. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses a neural network-based model for generating sentences. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves generating visual representations of sentences using linearized tree sequences.
